  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">okay...get gandalf, 12 power mofo by using glamdring, wizard is never late, prancing pony (for aragorn).  usually happens on 1st turn.  gimli stops the orc swarms, arwen stops the nazghul (and gwemegil helps get rid of all the extra weapon copies).  this deck goes to the other end of the spectrum by giving your opponent as many resources as you possibly can...hoping that they just cannot use them all.  usually they can&#39;t, and especially not on the first turn.  if you&#39;re unsure, just move one time first turn.  other than that, all the other random companions will take some hits for 12 power mofo, so you can just tighten your belt and trudge onward.  anyhoo....fun times at the beach. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
